results.Name: Red Panda
results.Comments:
My first attempt of a map (currently 3rd version) using only Basic editor (I was deciding whenever to buy the standard edition, did not decide yet).

[b]Idea of the map is based on Red Pandas and their... weird behaviour.
Hope you will have fun with the map.[/b]

There are 2 parts of the map - Black and White. Each has 2 checkpoints and you must complete both (one has speed check and the other one no-engine part).

There are some shortcuts:
[item]1 intended shortcut (end of Black path with enough speed)
[item]2 maybe-possible shortcuts (one on each half)
[item]A way to skip no-engine part (thanks to M1K3 but I am not sure it will be faster)

results.Name: IgNition
results.Comments:
I am pleased to annoounce the newest addition to my mappool.

[align=center][b]IgNition[/b][/align]

This map will challange you with some drifts, clean transitions.
For a good time, you will need to thread some corners and be very precise with your inputs.
Unconventionally there is no safe-risky fin, but the precise and risky lines you can decide to drive in the last part has a huge payoff potential. Thoose who don't let go of throttle will thrive in the end!

The  vanilla scenery adds a bit of spice to the othervise farely compplex route that uses some custom blocks.

It was a pleasure hunting for the author, feel like it is not easy, so hopefully it will be a challange for people who try to best me on the map.

Have a good hunting <3

results.Name: Wp 2
results.Comments:
I tried to build a nice huntable rpg with only block tech,
and I think I have succeeded, do not hesitate to give your feedback / criticism.
Have fun !

The map contains a small message transform into code for those who want to have fun,
finding it all the information is at the bottom
Info :
- Maping 30h
- 50 cp
- Discover 2-3h with complet code 4-5h (without Cam7)
- Only Vannila block On Grid (exept light & number) 
- Only tech transition/way
- no bonus/malus (boost/glider/engine off/ect...)
- Decoration mainly tech & water

All Cp contain :
- Numeroted
- Safe way
- Hard way
- Secret Code (the start also)

Almost Cp :
- Pixel way (need perfect previous cp)
- Cut (probably)

Warning :
- No stadium
- Almost hard way can't take, if previous cp is not good.
- some shadow bug

Secret code :
Every Cp & start contain a code forming a sentence once put together.
Every code is a Keyboard key for a letter or special character.

you can find the keyboard keys code that I used on this site :
https://asawicki.info/nosense/doc/devices/keyboard/key_codes.html

The codes on the cp are formed like this:
White number (corresponding to the number of the cp and to the place in the final sentence)
Red number (corresponding to Keyboard key code)
Ex : "17 90" for Cp 17 and letter Z
